      "settings": {
        "text_headline": "Welcome to the heimplanet family",
        "textarea_text": "Thank you for purchasing a Mono Series backpack and believing in our vision for a more sustainable future. In doing so you are joining us on an exciting journey towards more sustainable and eco-friendly backpack design.\n<br><br>\n<b>\"THE MOST ECO-FRIENDLY BAG WE CAN MAKE TODAY.”</b>"
      }
    },
    "l_content_right_MaMwry": {
      "type": "l_content_right",
      "settings": {
        "image_bild": "shopify://shop_images/Heimplanet-Mono-Series-Minimal-Pack-Diamond-Black-6_ddf03d32-fd92-46ce-9b47-5816238ce7c7.jpg",
        "text_headline": "this is why your<br>new bag is important",
        "textarea_text": "The textile industry significantly contributes to greenhouse gas emissions, resource use, and textile waste. Recycling can mitigate ecological impacts by saving water, energy, and chemicals and by reducing landfill use. Unfortunately, only a small percentage is currently recycled. \n<br><br>\nConventional backpacks typically contain a variety of materials such as nylon, polyester, PU, PE, EVA, metal, acetal, etc. This material diversity requires complex separation processes, which are energy-intensive and uneconomical. The answer to this problem lies in \"Design for Recycling\" concepts.\n<br><br>\nThank you for joining us in this critical endeavor. Together, we are driving progress forward, one"
      }
    },
    "l_content_left_dzUanx": {
      "type": "l_content_left",
      "settings": {
        "text_headline": "Circular Design",
        "textarea_text": "The bag you are holding is the result of over two years of R&D working together with leading material scientists from the Institute for Textile Technology at RWTH Aachen University and the Fraunhofer Institute for Chemical Technology. \n<br><br>\nOur Mono Series is a statement to our commitment to our continuous development towards positive change. We've designed these backpacks using our new and unique Dyecoshell™ Mono material, crafted from a single type of polyester. This ensures easy recyclability, significantly reducing environmental impact.\n<br><br>\nWhile <b>Ressource-Efficiency</b> and <b>Longevity</b> have been part of our design philosophy from the very beginning, the new Mono-Material-Concept allows us close the loop of our product lifecycle by ensuring full <b>Recyclability</b>.",
        "image_bild": "shopify://shop_images/Mono-material_Cycle_simplified.png"
      }
    },
    "l_grid_xawf9F": {
      "type": "l_grid",
      "blocks": {
