    "l_content_left_3nhLVM": {
      "type": "l_content_left",
      "settings": {
        "text_headline": "Prolonging the life cycle",
        "textarea_text": "Our mission is to promote sustainability by extending the life of our products. By focusing on proper use, care & maintenance, repair, and our Re-Store program, we aim to reduce waste and conserve resources. <br><br>Every step is designed to maximize a product's longevity, helping our customers make more sustainable choices. The longer a product lasts, the greater its positive impact on the environment.",
        "image_bild": "shopify://shop_images/Mono-material_Cycle_simple.png"
      }
    },
    "l_dropdowns_BzMTbG": {
      "type": "l_dropdowns",
      "blocks": {
        "dropdown_arce8n": {
          "type": "dropdown",
          "settings": {
            "image_icon": "shopify://shop_images/23-05-11_Icon_Motion2.png",
            "text_headline": "01 USE",
            "textarea_text": "All Heimplanet gear is made to last. There is no need to be overly cautious. However, in the spirit of getting the most out of your equipment we do want to give some tips on how to do so. \n<br><br>\n<b>Overloading / Overfilling</b>: <br>While all the bag's features are highly durable, overloading or overfilling your bag can put a strain on handles, seams and zippers and potentially reduce their lifespan. Simply pack mindfully and your bag will function even longer.\n\n<br><br>\n<b>Direct sunlight</b>: <br> Prolonged exposure to direct sunlight can cause fading and weaken the material over time. This of course doesnt mean that you can't travel so sunny places! Just if you are resting and you have the chance place your gear in the shade - your bag will thank you for it. \n<br><br>\n<b>Handling</b>:<br>Handle your bag with clean hands to avoid transferring oils and dirt. Be cautious with sharp objects to prevent scratches or tears.",
            "image_bild": "shopify://shop_images/Heimplanet-Transit-Line-Travel-Pack.jpg"
          }
        },
        "dropdown_UiLXPH": {
          "type": "dropdown",
          "settings": {
            "image_icon": "shopify://shop_images/23-05-11_Icon_Motion5.png",
            "text_headline": "02 CARE",
            "textarea_text": "<b>DO THIS </b> \n<br><br>\n\n<b>Cleaning:</b><br>\nWipe your bag regularly with a soft, dry cloth to remove dust. For deeper cleaning, use a damp cloth with mild soap, avoiding harsh chemicals. Alternatively, rinse the empty bag with lukewarm water using a gentle showerhead. Let it air dry completely before use or storage.\n<br><br>\n\n<b>Storage:</b><br>Keep your bag in a dust bag or pillowcase to protect from dust and light. Stuff it with tissue paper to maintain its shape, and avoid hanging, which can distort the form.\n\n<br><br>\n\n<b>Water Resistance Maintenance:</b><br>Over time, textiles may lose their water-repellent properties. Restore this by applying a PFAS-free water-repellent spray to a clean, dry bag. Allow it to dry fully. The internal coating is water-resistant, protecting contents even if the exterior loses some repellency.\n\n<br><br>\n<b>AVOID THIS</b><br><br>\n<b>No washing machine/dryer:</b> it can cause permanent damage.\n<br>\n<b>No ironing:</b> Heat can warp or melt synthetic fabrics.\n<br>\n<b>Excess Moisture:</b> Excessive water exposure can damage the exterior and interior.\n<br>\n<b>No harsh cleaners:</b> Avoid abrasive or chemical cleaners.\n<br>\n<b>Improper Storage:</b> Do not store in damp or unventilated spaces, which can cause mold and odors.",
            "image_bild": "shopify://shop_images/MonoSeries_MinimalPack_LifestyleShooting_LauritzKuntscher20.jpg"
          }
        },
        "dropdown_j9WAND": {
          "type": "dropdown",
          "settings": {
            "image_icon": "shopify://shop_images/23-05-11_Icon_Transit4.png",
            "text_headline": "03 Repair",
            "textarea_text": "Assess the Damage: Before starting any repairs, inspect your bag thoroughly to identify all areas that need attention, such as broken zippers, loose stitching, or tears in the fabric.\nStitching and Tears: For small tears or loose seams, use a needle and strong thread that matches the color of your bag. Carefully stitch the area, reinforcing any weak spots with extra stitches. We can recommend … \n+ Foto?\nZipper Repair: If a zipper is stuck, try lubricating it with a small amount of beeswax or graphite pencil. For broken zippers, you might need to replace the zipper entirely, which can be done at home with a zipper kit or by a professional.\n+ Foto?\nHandle and Strap Fixes: If a handle or strap is coming loose, reattach it using strong thread, ensuring the stitching is tight and secure. For more severe damage, consider replacing the handle or strap with a new one.\n+ Foto?\nHardware Replacement: If metal parts like clasps, buckles, or rivets are broken, you can often find replacement hardware at craft or repair stores. Use appropriate tools to remove the old hardware and attach the new pieces.\n+ Foto?\nProfessional Repair: If the damage is beyond your skills, consider taking it to a professional repair service or contact our HEIMPLANET service team. … can handle complex issues like lining replacement, extensive stitching, or custom hardware repair.",
            "image_bild": "shopify://shop_images/Moodbilder_CE_Commuter_001.jpg"
          }
        },
        "dropdown_mqQCmt": {
          "type": "dropdown",
          "settings": {
            "image_icon": "shopify://shop_images/Heimplanet-Re-Store-Icon-2024.png",
            "text_headline": "04 Re-store",
            "textarea_text": "The Heimplanet Re-Store Program offers a sustainable way to give your used Heimplanet bag a second life. Simply return your gently used bag to us, and in exchange, you'll receive a voucher that can be used toward your next purchase. Your returned bag will be cleaned, refurbished, and made available for resale, extending its lifecycle and reducing waste. This program not only helps the environment by promoting reuse but also rewards you for making eco-friendly choices. Use the contact formular below to join us in our commitment to sustainability and get rewarded for it!",
            "image_bild": "shopify://shop_images/Re-store.jpg"
          }
        },
        "dropdown_39zmPd": {
          "type": "dropdown",
          "settings": {
            "image_icon": "shopify://shop_images/Mono-Material-Endless-Black-Icon_4544ce44-09f8-4ab1-acf7-7c581edfa375.jpg",
            "text_headline": "05 Recycle",
            "textarea_text": "If your Heimplanet bag is too worn out to reuse, take advantage of our recycling program for Mono-packs. \nuse our contact form for further steps\nBilder die zeigen, wie Metallteile abgemacht werden\n(später: Upcycling produkt aus Versteller)",
